      },
      "date": "2012-11-21 18:02:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, approved\n\nIIRC, the libcfs_{pack,unpack}.h headers actually add some pragma for the structs that they surround, so need to be adjacent to the structs themselves.\n\nThat said, I don't _think_thst the Lustre wire protocol structs are misaligned or need explicit packing. Hopefully by the time (if ever) we get back to a Windows port their compiler will be smarter than it was a few years ago.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
